### Sediment content
![Pasted image 20221013131931.png](data:image/png;base64,)
- River activity has 3 types of load, called **stream load**
	- Bed load
		- Larger clastic material resting at the riverbed
		- Sand, gravel, and boulders
		- Move through:
			- Saltation (Bouncing)
			- Sliding
			- Rolling
		- Primary cause of erosion on landforms by rivers
	- Dissolved load
		- Ions dissolved in the water
	- Suspended load
		- Clastic particles suspended in the water
		- Typically silt and clay
